{% include "_letterhead.j2" %}

Re: Cease-of-contact demand under 15 U.S.C. §1692c(c)
Collector: {{ collection.collector_name or "the collection agency" }}
Original creditor: {{ collection.original_creditor or "(unknown)" }}
Alleged amount: ${{ "%.2f" % collection.alleged_amount }}

To whom it may concern,

Pursuant to 15 U.S.C. §1692c(c), I am notifying you in writing that
you must stop communicating with me regarding the above-referenced
debt. After receipt of this letter you may contact me only to:

  (1) advise me that further efforts are being terminated; or
  (2) notify me that you may invoke a specified remedy that you
      ordinarily invoke; or
  (3) notify me that you intend to invoke a specified remedy.

Any other communication — by phone, text, email, or in person, to me
or to any third party — will be treated as a per-instance violation
of the FDCPA and reported to the Consumer Financial Protection
Bureau, the Federal Trade Commission, and the attorney general of
{{ profile.state or collection.state or "my state" }}.

I do not waive any right to dispute the alleged debt under §1692g
or to dispute the reporting of this debt under the Fair Credit
Reporting Act.

Sincerely,


{{ profile.name }}
